{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.html#Nat.nthRoot.go\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">nthRoot</span>.<span class=\"name\">go</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">n </span><span class=\"fn\">a</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Auxiliary definition for `Nat.nthRoot`.\n\nGiven natural numbers `n`, `a`, `fuel`, `guess`\nsuch that `⌊(a : ℝ) ^ (1 / (n + 2) : ℝ)⌋₊ ≤ guess ≤ fuel`,\nreturns `⌊(a : ℝ) ^ (1 / (n + 2) : ℝ)⌋₊`.\n\nThe auxiliary number `guess` is the current approximation in Newton's method,\ntracked in the arguments so that the definition uses a tail recursion\nwhich is unfolded into a loop by the compiler.\n\nThe auxiliary number `fuel` is an upper estimate on the number of steps in Newton's method.\nAny number `fuel ≥ guess` is guaranteed to work, but smaller numbers may work as well.\nIf `fuel` is too small, then `Nat.nthRoot.go` returns the result of the `fuel`th step\nof Newton's method.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.html#Nat.nthRoot.go","kind":"def","line":44,"name":"Nat.nthRoot.go","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.lean#L44-L48"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.html#Nat.nthRoot\"><span class=\"name\">Nat</span>.<span class=\"name\">nthRoot</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Nat\">Nat</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`Nat.nthRoot n a = ⌊(a : ℝ) ^ (1 / n : ℝ)⌋₊` defined in terms of natural numbers.\n\nWe use Newton's method to find a root of $x^n = a$,\nso it converges superexponentially fast. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.html#Nat.nthRoot","kind":"def","line":19,"name":"Nat.nthRoot","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/a3a10db0e9d66acbebf76c5e6a135066525ac900/Mathlib/Data/Nat/NthRoot/Defs.lean#L19-L48"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Init"],"instances":[],"name":"Mathlib.Data.Nat.NthRoot.Defs"}